            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.4"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="italics">Good Mornings Start with....</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">THE</hi> <hi rend="italics">Sun</hi> <hi rend="caps">SENTINEL</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    2501 <hi rend="caps">N.</hi> Federal Highway
                    Pompano Beach, Fla. 33061
                    941-7800
                        <lb/>
                    855 <hi rend="caps">S.</hi> Federal Highway
                    Room 101-<hi rend="caps">A</hi>
                    Boca Raton, Fla. 33432
                    395-5950
                        <lb/>
                    314 <hi rend="caps">N. E.</hi> 6th Avenue 
                    Delray Beach, Fla. 33344
                    278-2676
                        <lb/>
                    416 <hi rend="caps">N.</hi> Dixie Highway
                    Lake Worth, Fla. 33460 
                    585-5581
                </fw>
                
                <note>ans. 6/5/72</note>
                
                <opener>
                    855 <hi rend="caps">S.</hi> Federal Highway 
                    Boca Raton, Fla. 33432
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>English Department</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Please allow me to tell you how much I enjoyed reading your <hi rend="underline">Cycle Of The West.</hi></p>
                    
                <p>Although I never enjoyed poetic narratives during college several years ago, I have read your cycle twice and am beginning it for the third time.</p>
                
                <p>I know it must seem strange to you to have written it over 40 years ago and to receive a response now, but I just discovered you four weeks ago.</p>
                
                <p>During my weekly browsing through the stacks in the Fort Lauderdale library for something to read, I found your poetry.</p> 
                
                <p>Since then I have ordered both volumes of the cycle from the University of Nebraska in addition to three other books that you have written.</p> 
                
                <fw>1</fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.5"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">5</fw>
                <fw type="authorial">-Two-</fw>
                
                <p>The test of good literature is if it says something to generations decades after it is written.</p>
                
                <p>Your capturing of the agony of a people loosing<sic>losing</sic> the world they have known and their need to be treated as humans proves the lastingness of your poetry.</p> 
                
                <p>As long as man's misunderstanding of each other and feelings of superiority over those different from him exists, your poetry will burst forth as new a<del>d</del><add>s</add> the day it was written each time someone discovers you for the first time.</p> 
                
                <p>No narrative or poetic account of the death of Crazy Horse that I have read since discovering your account has captured the emotion of the tragedy better than you have.</p> 
                
                <p>I mentioned your name to one of the other reporters, who is from the midwest, and he said you appeared on the Dick Cavett television program. Hopefully he will rebroadcast the program sometime in the futu<del>f</del><add>r</add>e.</p> 
                
                <p>Again allow me to thank you for contributing so much to literature and to wish you a happy and successful year.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Robert D. Paslay</signed>
                    <signed>Robert D. Paslay</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw>1.</fw>
                
            </div1>
